requiredCourses.name: Business Applications Programming
requiredCourses.description: Introduction to computer applications in business. Programming exercises in COBOL.   CL: 2020.

requiredCourses.name: Data Structures and Algorithms
requiredCourses.description: Techniques for representing and processing information, including the use of lists, trees, and graphs; analysis of algorithms; sorting, searching, and hashing techniques.   FS: 12/07/2016.   CL: 2020.

requiredCourses.name: Introduction to Computer Networks
requiredCourses.description: Concepts and components of computer networks and the Internet; network applications; network protocol stack.   FS: 10/5/2016.   CL: 2020.

requiredCourses.name: Capstone Computing Project I
requiredCourses.description: Major team-based software design project to be undertaken in a student’s final year of study; project planning, software requirements analysis, design, and specification. Written reports and oral presentations in a technical setting.   FS: 09/09/2020.   CL: 2020.

requiredCourses.name: Capstone Computing Project II
requiredCourses.description: Continuation of CSCE 490. Computer system implementation, testing, verification and validation of results. Written reports and oral presentations in a technical setting.   FS: 12/07/2022.

requiredCourses.name: Database System Design
requiredCourses.description: Database management systems; database design and implementation; security, integrity, and privacy.   CL: 2020.

requiredCourses.name: Information Security Principles
requiredCourses.description: Threats to information resources and appropriate countermeasures. Cryptography, identification and authentication, access control models and mechanisms, multilevel database security, steganography, Internet security, and intrusion detection and prevention.   FS: 09/14/2016.   CL: 2020.

requiredCourses.name: Strategic Management of Information Systems
requiredCourses.description: Strategic management and use of information systems in organizations.   FS: 12/05/2018.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Critical Reading and Composition
classesInPlan.description: Instruction in strategies for critically reading and analyzing literature and non-literary texts; structured, sustained practice in composing expository and analytical essays.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Calculus I
classesInPlan.description: Functions, limits, derivatives, introduction to integrals, the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus, applications of derivatives and integrals. Four classroom hours and one laboratory hour per week.    CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Algorithmic Design I
classesInPlan.description: Problem-solving, algorithmic design, and programming. Three lectures and two laboratory hours per week.   FS: 12/04/2013.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Computing in the Modern World
classesInPlan.description: An introduction to the field of computing: trends in computing technology, the profession, and careers; subdisciplines in computing; the nature of research and development.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Rhetoric and Composition
classesInPlan.description: Instruction and intensive practice in researching, analyzing, and composing written arguments about academic and public issues.   FS: 12/7/2016.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Introduction to Astronomy
classesInPlan.description: An introduction to the solar system and universe accomplished with interactive lectures, demonstrations, and laboratory experience.  Designed primarily for the non-science major.    FS: 11/04/2020.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Algorithmic Design II
classesInPlan.description: Continuation of CSCE 145. Rigorous development of algorithms and computer programs; elementary data structures. Three lecture hours and two laboratory hours per week.   FS: 12/04/2013.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: UNIX/Linux Fundamentals
classesInPlan.description: UNIX operating system, user-level system commands, and programming tools. UNIX scripting languages.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Biological Principles I
classesInPlan.description: Introductory survey of macromolecules, cell structure and function, genetics, and molecular biology.   FS: 10/07/2020.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Introduction to Art
classesInPlan.description: Introduction to art appreciation. Elements and principles of the visual arts, with examples from the history of art.   FS: 09/09/2020.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Business Applications Programming
classesInPlan.description: Introduction to computer applications in business. Programming exercises in COBOL.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Computer Hardware Foundations
classesInPlan.description: Number representation, data formats, CPU and memory organization, assembly language, I/O and peripherals, computer networks. Students may not apply both CSCE 210 and CSCE 212 to any minor or major program of study.   FS: 11/04/2020.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Software Engineering
classesInPlan.description: Fundamentals of software design and development; software implementation strategies; object-oriented design techniques; functional design techniques; design patterns; design process; source control; testing.    FS: 12/6/2017.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Introduction to Economics
classesInPlan.description: Introduction to economics principles for non-majors. Basics of supply and demand and government and monetary policy are covered in a non-technical manner. Not open to business or economics students. Credit not granted for both ECON 223 and ECON 221 or ECON 222.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Online Public Communication
classesInPlan.description: Introduction to theory and practice of live and recorded online spoken communication in public, social, and institutional contexts. Training in invention, performance, and critical analysis of online spoken communication, including audience analysis, persuasion, delivery, and ethical engagement. Includes significant practice in preparing and presenting live online public communication.   FS: 12/7/2016.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Introduction to Computer Security
classesInPlan.description: Introduction to the theory and practice of computer security, including security policies, authentification, digital certificates, firewalls, malicious code, legal and ethical issues, and incident handling.   FS:  4/5/2017.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Advanced Programming Techniques
classesInPlan.description: Pointers; memory management; advanced programming language structures: operator overloading, iterators, multiple inheritance, polymorphism, templates, virtual functions; Unix programming environment.   FS: 12/6/2017.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Discrete Mathematics for Computer Science
classesInPlan.description: Logic, number theory, sequences, series, recursion, mathematical induction, set theory, enumeration, functions, relations, graphs and trees. Connections to computers and to programming are emphasized when possible.   FS: 11/04/2020.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Computer Information Systems in Business
classesInPlan.description: An introduction to the effective use of information systems tools in day-to-day business communications, analysis, and decision making.

classesInPlan.name: Introduction to African-American Studies
classesInPlan.description: Introduction to the analysis and discussion of creative works and traditions by and about African Americans through folklore, music, art, dance, and literature.

classesInPlan.name: Data Structures and Algorithms
classesInPlan.description: Techniques for representing and processing information, including the use of lists, trees, and graphs; analysis of algorithms; sorting, searching, and hashing techniques.   FS: 12/07/2016.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Professional Issues in Computer Science and Engineering
classesInPlan.description: Professional issues in the information technology professions; history and social context of computing; professional responsibilities; privacy; intellectual property; risks and liabilities of computer-based systems.   FS: 04/02/2014.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Statistical Methods I
classesInPlan.description: Applications and principles of elementary probability, essential discrete and continuous probability distributions, sampling distributions, estimation, and hypothesis testing. Inference for means, variances, proportions, one-way ANOVA, simple linear regression, and contingency tables. Statistical packages such as SAS or R.  May not be taken concurrently with or after STAT 509, STAT 513, or STAT 516. Not for CAS, MAS, MS, or PhD credit in Statistics.    FS: 12/02/2015.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Survey of Accounting
classesInPlan.description: Survey of accounting topics related to business decisions including financial reporting, managerial accounting, and other special topics.   FS: 09/10/2014.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Principles of Management
classesInPlan.description: A comprehensive survey of the basic principles of management applicable to all forms of business. The course provides the student with a basis for thinking about complex business situations in the framework of analysis of the management process.

classesInPlan.name: Business Writing
classesInPlan.description: Extensive practice in different types of business writing, from brief letters to formal articles and reports.   FS: 06/06/2018.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Database System Design
classesInPlan.description: Database management systems; database design and implementation; security, integrity, and privacy.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Strategic Management of Information Systems
classesInPlan.description: Strategic management and use of information systems in organizations.   FS: 12/05/2018.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Statistical Methods II
classesInPlan.description: Applications and principles of linear models. Simple and multiple linear regression, analysis of variance for basic designs, multiple comparisons, random effects, and analysis of covariance. Statistical packages such as SAS. Not for CAS, MAS, MS, or PhD credit in Statistics.   FS: 12/02/2015.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Survey of Commercial Law
classesInPlan.description: Basic legal concepts and the judicial system, with emphasis on business law.

classesInPlan.name: United States History to 1865
classesInPlan.description: A general survey of the United States from the era of discovery to 1865, emphasizing major political, economic, social, and intellectual developments.     FS: 06/02/2021.

classesInPlan.name: Issues in Economics
classesInPlan.description: The nature and causes of major economic problems facing the nation and its communities, and policy alternatives designed to solve them. The philosophy and methodology of economics in social problem solving.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Introduction to Classical Mythology
classesInPlan.description: Major gods, goddesses, heroes, and heroines of classical mythology as portrayed in major literary works; the function of myth in society and its relevance to modern life.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Capstone Computing Project II
classesInPlan.description: Continuation of CSCE 490. Computer system implementation, testing, verification and validation of results. Written reports and oral presentations in a technical setting.   FS: 12/07/2022.

classesInPlan.name: Management of Information Technology
classesInPlan.description: Overview of current practices and trends in end-user technology and information system management.   FS: 10/03/2018.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: World Literature
classesInPlan.description: Selected masterpieces of world literature from antiquity to present.   CL: 2020.

classesInPlan.name: Exploring Religion
classesInPlan.description: Beliefs and practices of the world's religions and the methods scholars use to study them.   FS: 02/03/2016.   CL: 2020.

applicationArea.description: Database management systems; database design and implementation; security, integrity, and privacy.   CL: 2020.

applicationArea.name: Artificial Intelligence
applicationArea.description: Heuristic problem solving, theorem proving, and knowledge representation, including the use of appropriate programming languages and tools.   CL: 2020.

applicationArea.name: Big Data Analytics
applicationArea.description: Foundational techniques and tools required for data science and big data analytics.  Concepts, principles, and techniques applicable to any technology and industry for establishing a baseline that can be enhanced by future study.   FS: 12/03/2014.   CL: 2020.
